-- Mauritius Lux Set for Longest Period of Gains in Nine Months
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-03-26T07:27:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/mauritius-lux-set-for-longest-period-of-gains-in-nine-months.html
Lux Island Resorts Ltd. (NRL) , the third-
biggest leisure operator by market value in Mauritius, is headed
for its longest rising streak in almost nine months.  The  stock  advanced 0.3 rupee, or 1.4 percent, to 21.30
rupees by 11:15 a.m. in Port Louis trading, a fifth straight
trading day of gains. It’s set for its longest run of gains
since June 29.  A close at this level would be the stock’s strongest since
Feb. 28, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
